{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2015}} {{Infobox scientist | honorific_prefix = | name = Eldridge M. Moores | image = | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = October 13, 1938 | birth_place = [[Phoenix, Arizona]], U.S. | death_date = {{death date and age|2018|10|28|1938|10|13}} | death_place = [[California]], U.S. | death_cause = | fields = [[Tectonics]] | workplaces = [[University of California, Davis]] | education = {{ublist|[[California Institute of Technology]] (B.S.)|[[Princeton University|Princeton]] (Ph.D.)}} | alma_mater = | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | doctoral_advisor = Harry Hess | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | influences = | influenced = | awards = {{ublist | Doctor of Science ([[Honoris Causa]]), [[College of Wooster]] (1996) | Distinguished Service Award, [[Geological Society of America]] (1988) | Fellow, American Association for the Advancement of Science (1992) | Geological Association of Canada Medal (1994) | Fellow, [[California Academy of Sciences]] (1996) | Honorary Fellow, [[Geological Society of London]] (1997) | [[Geological Society of America]]/International Division Distinguished Career Award (2006)}}
| author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = | children = | footnotes = }}
'''Eldridge Moores''' (October 13, 1938 – October 28, 2018) was an [[United States|American]] [[geologist]].<ref name="UCD">{{Cite web |url=https://geology.ucdavis.edu/people/inmemoriam/moores |title=Eldridge M. Moores (1938-2018) |website=UC Davis Earth and Planetary Sciences |language=en |access-date=2018-11-02}}</ref> He specialized in the understanding of [[ophiolites]] (fragments of [[oceanic crust]] and mantle that have been emplaced onto the [[continental crust]]) and the geology of the continental crust of the Western [[United States]] and Tethyan belt, the geology of [[Greece]], [[Cyprus]], and [[Pakistan]], and the tectonic development of the [[Sierra Nevada (U.S.)|Sierra Nevada]] and the Alpine - Himalayan systems.<ref name="UCD" />
Moores was Distinguished Professor Emeritus of Geology at the [[University of California, Davis]].<ref name="UCD" />
In 1996, Moores was President of the [[Geological Society of America]] (GSA)<ref>GSA Past Leaders http://www.geosociety.org/GSA/About/Leadership/Past_Leaders/GSA/About/Past_Leaders.aspx</ref> and editor of the society's journal [[Geology (journal)|''Geology'']] from 1981 to 1989. He is the recipient of the GSA's Distinguished Service Award and the Geological Association of Canada Medal.<ref>http://www.geosociety.org/awards/06speeches/international.htm</ref>
Together with geologist [[Robert J. Twiss]], Moores co-authored two textbooks: ''Tectonics''<ref>''Tectonics'', W. H. Freeman (1995); {{ISBN|9780716724377}}</ref> and ''Structural Geology''<ref>''Structural Geology'', Macmillan Higher Education (2006); {{ISBN|9780716749516}}</ref>
Moores is the main subject of the [[John McPhee]] book on California geology, ''Assembling California'' (1993),<ref>''Assembling California'' (1998); Farrar, Straus and Giroux / [http://us.macmillan.com/assemblingcalifornia/johnmcphee Macmillan] (1993); {{ISBN|9780374523930}}</ref> as well as McPhee's ''[[Annals of the Former World]]'' (1998).<ref>''Annals of the Former World'', John McPhee; Farrar Straus & Giroux, New York, NY (1998); {{ISBN|9780374105204}}</ref>
In 2013, Eldridge Moores was awarded the title of UC Davis distinguished professor emeritus. This title is awarded annually by the UC Davis Emeriti Association on the basis of outstanding contributions following retirement in the traditional areas of teaching, research and service.<ref>http://www.davisenterprise.com/local-news/ucd/eldridge-moores-name-distinguished-professor-emeritus/</ref>
